data.title: About: Sommatiwongse Varodaya
data.meta_description: Prince Sommatiwongse Varodaya, The Prince of Nakhon Si Thammarat (Thai: สมมุติวงศ์วโรทัย; RTGS: Sommuttiwong Warothai) was the Prince of Siam (later Thailand He was a member of Siamese royal family is a son of King Chulalongkorn Rama V of Siam. His mother was Queen Savang Vadhana, a daughter of King Mongkut (thus his father's half-sister) and Princess Piyamavadi Prince Sommatiwongse Varodaya died on 17 June 1899 at the age 17.
